#4135
Natural Stone Cavern, Smithy~
Unlike most of Tirath Regnus, this small room beside the <xx> is lit
entirely by torches.  Any sparks from a forge or the worker's hammers
could easily ignite any oil lamps present and cause an explosion. 
Elaboratly carved stone gargoyles grasp the torches in hand, keeping them
from tumbling to the floor.  Spiraling up to an unseen landing above are
stairs made from sturdy oaken struts and heavy stone slabs.  A forge
burns north of here and casts a soft orange glow upon the floor.  Carved
from the smoothe stone floor is a two-dwarf-step wide groove which
carries overflow water back to the river.  Wooden pallets lay across the
channel for pedestrians.
~
[Glynis] smithy is operated by machinery breif desc follows
[Glynis] underground waterfall north, buckets are strung on pully system
[Glynis] buckets can hold two dwarves (size)
[Glynis] buckets catch water from falls, water weight turns pully
[Glynis] buckets are dumped down a tube which lead to troughs in the smithy
[Glynis] troughs are kept full of clean cool water this way
[Glynis] water automatically drains off back into the river
[Glynis] pullys also turn fans which fan fires, eliminating the need for bellows
