torches~
These torches are small oak branches whose tops are wrapped with a cloth
soaked in lamp oil.  They are about waist-high on a dwarf, and thick as
an adult grass snake.  All the bark has been whittled away and sanded
down making for a smooth outter surface.  Occasionally, small bits of ash
ride a draft up to the ceiling leaving a glowing spiral trail behind.
~
E
stone gargoyles carved~
The work of a master stonecutter, these gargoyles are carved with such
intricacy that they are easily mistaken for the real thing.  Crimson
gems, the size of a perfect skipping stone and flawlessly cut, are inset
between their eyelids.  Rather unlike traditional gargoyles, the faces on
these are carved in a less than evil manner -- most are yawning or
grinning happily.  Each is about the size of a troll's fist and set at
dwarf eye level on the cavern wall.
~
E
stairs spiral oaken~
Green-streaked blocks of grey stone have been chiseled into dwarf-sized
steps.  Oaken struts, adorned with jagged decorative carvings, support
the heavy stones.  They swirl up around a heavily polished pillar of
marble.
~
